{{Economy of Turkey}}
'''Blue Tunnel Project''', is an effort to provide large-scale irrigation to arid lands of [[Konya Plain]], in the [[Anatolia|Turkish heartland]], where agriculture and [[wildlife]] are under threat.<ref>[http://www.dailysabah.com/nation/2015/05/22/turkeys-arid-heart-to-bloom-after-irrigation-project Turkey's arid heart to bloom after irrigation project]</ref><ref>[http://www.aa.com.tr/en/headline/106994--blue-tunnel-to-connect-konya-plain-with-potable-water Blue Tunnel to connect Konya Plain with potable water]</ref>

Blue Tunnel, the most important part of the [[Konya Plain Project]], is the second-largest irrigation scheme of Turkey after the [[Southeastern Anatolia Project]] (GAP),<ref>[http://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/second-largest-irrigation-project-opens-in-central-anatolia.aspx?pageID=238&nID=82822&NewsCatID=341 Second-largest irrigation project opens in Central Anatolia]</ref> and aims to provide the region with a yearly 414 million cubic meters of water.<ref>[http://www.ilci.com.tr/en/sectors/construction/tunnels-construction/37-mavi-tuneli-insaati.html Blue Tunnel Construction]</ref>

