A Central Forest Reserve is a body of forest or woodland managed by the [[National Forestry Authority]] (NFA) under the National Forestry and Tree Planting Act 8/2003.<ref>[http://www.nema-ug.org/regulations/forestry_tree_planting_act.pdf Uganda National Forestry Tree Planting Act 8/2003]{{dead link|date=November 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> The NFA is mandated to manage all 506 Central Forest Reserves in Uganda.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nfa.org.ug |title=National Forestry Authority |publisher=Nfa.org.ug |date=2011-11-08 |accessdate=2013-07-21}}</ref> These reserves are part of the [[List of Protected Areas in Uganda|protected areas of Uganda]]. The total area of land covered is 12,657.47&nbsp;km² or 6.3% of the total land area of [[Uganda]].<ref>[http://www.nfa.org.ug/docs/forests_functions_and_classification.pdf "Forests Functions and Classification," National Forest Augthority of Uganda] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120906023450/http://nfa.org.ug/docs/forests_functions_and_classification.pdf |date=2012-09-06 }}</ref> They compose of natural forest like [[Albertine Rift montane forests|moist semi-deciduous forests]] and forest plantations mainly of [[pine]] and [[eucalyptus]] species. Legal activities done under the NFA are [[Forestry in Uganda|harvesting timber]], re-planting and tourism.
