{{about|a proposed indirect coal-to-liquids plant project between Sasol and Shenhua|a direct coal-to-liquid plant owned by Shenhua|Erdos CTL}} '''Shenhua CTL''' (also known as '''Ningxia Hui CTL''', {{zh|神华CTL}}) is a planned [[coal liquefaction]] plant in Ningdong, [[Ningxia]], [[China]]. Its planned capacity is {{convert|80000|oilbbl/d}}.<ref name=upstream220609/><ref> {{cite news |url=http://www.steelguru.com/news/index/2008/08/30/NjA4MzA%3D/Sasol_and_Shenhua_to_focus_on_Ningxia_Hui_CTL_feasibility_study.html |title= Sasol and Shenhua to focus on Ningxia Hui CTL feasibility study | publisher = SteelGuru | date = 2008-08-30 | accessdate = 2009-08-02}} </ref> The liquefaction plant is to use a Sasol's indirect liquefaction technology, based on the [[Fischer–Tropsch process]].
The feasibility study was carried out by [[Foster Wheeler]] and Wuhuan Engineering.<ref name=upstream221008> {{cite news | url = http://www.upstreamonline.com/live/article165207.ece | title = Shenhua CTL under starters' orders | newspaper = [[Upstream (newspaper)|Upstream Online]] | first = Anthea | last = Pitt | publisher = [[NHST Media Group]] | date = 2008-10-22 | accessdate = 2009-08-02 | id = {{subscription required}}}} </ref><ref name=downstream271008> {{cite news | url = http://www.downstreamtoday.com/news/article.aspx?a_id=13469 | title = Foster Wheeler To Perform CTL Study In China | publisher = Downstream Today | date = 2008-10-27 | accessdate = 2009-08-02}} </ref> The constriction is to start in October 2010 and it expected to cost US$7&nbsp;billion.<ref name=upstream220609> {{cite news | url = http://www.upstreamonline.com/live/article181528.ece | title = Sasol and Shenhua prime CTL pumps | newspaper = [[Upstream (newspaper)|Upstream Online]] | publisher = [[NHST Media Group]] | date = 2009-06-22 | accessdate = 2009-08-02 | id = {{subscription required}}}} </ref> The project was developed by [[Sasol]] and Ningxia Coal Industry Group, a subsidiary of [[Shenhua Group]].<ref name=upstream220609/><ref name=upstream221008/> The agreement between companies was signed on 21 June 2006.<ref name=upstream230606> {{cite news | url = http://www.upstreamonline.com/live/article112342.ece | title = Sasol carrying out Chinese CTL studies | newspaper = [[Upstream (newspaper)|Upstream Online]] | publisher = [[NHST Media Group]] | date = 2006-06-23 | accessdate = 2009-08-02 | id = {{subscription required}}}} </ref> In September 2011, Sasol pull back from the project.<ref name=engineering120911>Shenhua completed the construction and has started up the CTL plant. {{cite news | url = http://www.engineeringnews.co.za/article/sasol-pulls-back-from-china-ctl-reallocates-capital-and-people-2011-09-12 | title = Sasol pulls back from China CTL, reallocates capital and people | newspaper = Engineering News | first = Terence | last = Creamer | date = 2011-09-12 | accessdate = 2012-03-10}} </ref>
