'''Tarcísio Feitosa da Silva''' is a prominent [[environmental activist]] from [[Brazil]], where he is director of the Roman Catholic Church's Pastoral Land Commission. Because of his work with local communities deep in the [[Amazon Rainforest|Amazon]] jungle in their struggle against illegal commercial [[logging]] and [[mining]] operations, "after the American nun [[Dorothy Stang]] was shot to death on a jungle road, he replaced her at the top of the death list that loggers, ranchers, miners and land speculators are known to maintain."

In 2006, Mr. da Silva was a recipient of the [[Goldman Environmental Prize]].

